// Psi Aeterna IV - PvE Boss god 1 (god-pve)
// (Volatile Launch, Quick Launch, Linear Compensator), (Tactical Mag, Appended Mag), (Blast Distributor, Stats for All), (One for All)
//notes:Inspired by @Saint_Kabr, @CourtProjects and @ImpetusAlways (PvE PvE-Boss PvE-BurstDamage PvE-EndGame PvE-God M+KB Controller): First-choice PvE roll for burst DPS against Banes, Elites, Champions or Minibosses, or shorter boss DPS windows in both general at-level or better, and end-game underleveled content. Nox Sidereal IV is a micro-missile pulse rifle, which are rated S-Tier for endgame PvE by @TheAegisRelic tiering spreadsheet https://linktr.ee/TheAegisRelic still offering excellent and easy super-generating damage even post-nerf. The frame intrinsic shoots micro-missiles that track locked-on enemies as per the https://www.destiny2.science/ Destiny Data Compendium. The stats are good by comparison with its peer - hopefully when the website's back https://d2foundry.gg/w/3556730800 will show how the weapon stats impact in-game performance. There's a couple of ways to go with the barrel perk - boost Blast Radius, Handling or Velocity, or maybe a bit of everything, and use the magazine perk to boost mag size. While there's no truly bad rolls, to optimise for burst damage in the first trait perk column Blast Distributor stacks up to ×5 to provide +10 to your Grenade attribute (+13 when enhanced) per stack on explosive damage a total of +50 (+65 enhanced) for a refreshable 5s on further explosive damage which is great for Warlock buddy builds, and additional grenade damage on targets. Alternatively, when you're using One for All in the second column which boosts damage by ×1.35 for a non-refreshable 10s (11s when enhanced), Stats for All boosts gunfeel stats on the same proccing condition - hitting three separate targets within 3s of each. For this roll, you might be lucky and get the rare Accelerated Assault origin trait, which passively refills 10% of the magazine, and boosts damage by ×1.05 for getting 3 hits within a 1.6s window. Otherwise, Wild Card provides the chance of Telesto-like "Experimental Submunitions" dropping on a kill - the number depends on the enemy tier - that last up to 10.5s and explode on contact or proximity to an enemy. Of less interest is Vanguard Vindication which provides up to ×3 stacks that reduces incoming damage at max to ×0.94 for a refreshable 10s (12.5s when enhanced), on kills within 20s of using a class ability. If you're interested, "Psi Aeterna" combines the Greek letter Psi (Ψ) with the Latin word Aeterna, which together roughly translate to "Eternal Soul" or "Unending Mind". Recommended MW: Blast Radius, Handling or Velocity, with your preferred choice of mod to boost weapon stats, ammo generation, or elemental pickups for builds - and don't forget to check any available seasonal fragile mods.|tags:PvE PvE-Boss PvE-BurstDamage PvE-EndGame PvE-God M+KB Controller
