// Hawthorne's Field-Forged Shotgun - PvE Utility god 1
// (Barrel Shroud, Smallbore, Full Choke, Corkscrew Rifling), (Tactical Mag, Appended Mag, Assault Mag), (Slideshot, Grave Robber, Threat Detector, Lead from Gold), (Chill Clip)
//notes:Inspired by @Saint_Kabr, @CourtProjects and @ImpetusAlways (PvE PvE-Utility PvE-EndGame PvE-God M+KB Controller): First-choice PvE utility roll in both general at-level or better, and end-game underleveled content, particularly with Stasis builds. Hawthorne's Field-Forged Shotgun is now a lightweight shotgun, which are rated C-Tier for endgame PvE by @TheAegisRelic tiering spreadsheet https://linktr.ee/TheAegisRelic offering high QoL given its bonuses but an awful damage profile. The frame intrinsic offers +20 to Mobility and ×1.0625 base movement speed as per the https://www.destiny2.science/ Destiny Data Compendium. The stats are below average by comparison with its peers - hopefully when the website's back https://d2foundry.gg/w/3421075982 will show how the weapon stats impact in-game performance. Use the barrel perk to Handling or Range, or maybe tighten pellet spread, and then with the magazine perk you'll want something that improves magazine size, or Assault Mag improves RPM. As the damage profile isn't great, for end-game use, Chill Clip in the second trait perk column is the play to disrupt Overload Champions and control tougher adds, applying +60 stacks of Stasis Slow (freezing targets after 2 hits) within a 4m AoE for 4s on a hit - 8s with Whisper of Durance - with ammo in the top half of the base mag size. To help keep the mag topped out for Chill Clip, first column refill and reload perks like Slideshot, Grave Robber or Threadt Detector make sense. Alternatively Lead from Gold is always a top-tier perk, saving on Ammo Generation, Scavenger and Finder mods. The Field-Tested origin trait starts subtly but if you can stay alive to get kills, you'll start to feel the gunfeel stat boosts as you get to the higher stacks. Recommended MW: Handling, with your preferred choice of mod to boost weapon stats, ammo generation, or elemental pickups for builds - and don't forget to check any available seasonal fragile mods.|tags:PvE PvE-Utility PvE-EndGame PvE-God M+KB Controller
